comm: length delivery on the off stump, Rahane guides it towards third man easily
leans forward a bit to help the length delivery to point
back of length towards the hips and it's tucked away towards square leg for one
slightly fuller towards the off stump, pushed down to mid off, off the front foot
touch wider outside off and he leans forward to push to cover now
much wider outside off and Rahane chases it with a big lean outside and misses. Very very risky early on
angled in from short of length towards leg, helped to fine leg for one
nice line this time outside off, just back of length and he leaves it alone
back of length again outside off and left easily
length delivery towards off now, pushed down to mid-on this time
length delivery on off without much pace, pushed back
back of length outside off, Vijay cuts and gets an inside edge on the pads
length delivery on off, he leans forward and pushes into the covers
errs down the leg side for a wide now
middle-stump line now from wide of the crease, Rahane stays back and tucks it to midwicket
wider outside off, there's room and Rahane drives that away from the body through the covers for four
back to good-length closer to off and it's pushed back
pushes this one with soft hands a bit wide of mid-off for a quick single
on length on off now, he defends it back
angled in from back of length, helped to the leg side for one
length delivery just outside off, he defends it back
drives it nicely into the covers and Raza dives to his right to save a few runs. Great effort
back of length now outside off and it's punched straight to cover
gets this one inside from outside off, Vijay shoulders arms
touch fuller outside off and pushed down to mid-off gently
slightly full and wide and Rahane leans into it to unleash another drive for four
good-length ball now and it's pushed into the covers
straighter delivery on length and it's turned down to mid-on for a quick single
bit of room outside off and Vijay helps it towards point for another quick single
on length on the off stump, pushed down gently to mid-off
on length on off stump, pushed down to mid-on off the front foot
pretty wide outside off and it's driven straight to extra cover
slightly full just outside off, it's turned late to fine leg for one
beaten this time as the ball angles in towards the pads as Rahane came forward but missed
takes a step forward and pushes the ball to extra cover
bit of width outside off and Rahane cuts it nicely to third man for one
presses forward and blocks the bell towards mid-on and calls for a quick single
wide enough outside off to be left alone by Vijay
bit of swing as this one comes in closer to off and Vijay leaves again
nipping in again as Vijay's bat turns while playing the shot and he gets an edge to midwicket for one
targets the off stump and Rahane pushes it down to mid-off
comes down and drives the ball with a full face of the bat, straight back and mid-off gets a hand to deflect the ball for one
goes down the leg side to the keeper, some players yell "catch" as there was some sound, it's called a wide though. Maybe it was of bat hitting pad
beautiful shot! He came down a step and creamed that overpitched delivery well outside off, through the covers for four
pretty wide outside off and it's left alone easily
shuffles across to the off side and steers the ball towards mid-on for a quick one
comes down a step and looks to steer that on off but gets a bottom edge back to the bowler
on length, outside off, he doesn't want to play that one
touch closer to the batsman and defends it towards cover point but no time for a run
back of length and angled in, turns it to mid-on off the back foot
length delivery on the off stump, pushed a bit wide of mid-on for one
short of length now outside off and Rahane helps it a bit wide of point for one more
fuller and closer to off stump, driven nice and straight to extra cover
this one nips in from outside off, Vijay waits and guides it late towards cover point
fullish outside the off stump, pushed to point this time
angled in towards the pads and it's driven away wide of mid-on for one
pretty wide outside off, he drives with a big swing, bigger than what we have seen from him this morning, and it goes to third man
another big drive, this time from Rahane and it flies away to third man
bit of room offered and Vijay drives it wide of cover point with sheer timing, not much power, for four
angled in this time and it's helped to fine leg for one
touch back of length just outside off, punches to the covers
slightly back of length outside off, helps it to third man for one
takes a step down and lets the ball go well outside off
more accurate - angled in towards off stump and Rahane defends off the back foot
well outside off on length, he leaves it again
seaming in from back of length towards the batsman, he comes forward and defends it back
fuller outside off, not much pace and it's pushed down to mid-off
bit of room and rising on off, Vijay cuts in the air and it falls just short of the point fielder. Misfield also gives them point
fuller this time and Vijay drives it square of the wicket to deep point
into the pads and Rahane helps it wide of square leg for two in the gap
back of length towards middle stump, he fails to time this properly to the leg side
back of length delivery angled in, tucked with the angle to fine leg
on length outside off and it's steered to point. They look for a run but there's no time
short ball outside off, Rahane chases with a horizontal bat and gets a bottom edge past the off stump and the keeper to fine leg
swing and a miss! Rahane walks down, the ball swings away from length as he looked to drive and was beaten by the movement, called wide though
back of length outside off with some outswing, left alone
back of length again and it's punched to deep cover this time for one
angles it in and it's helped to fine leg for one
full delivery well outside off, Rahane watches it go to the keeper
pretty full on off, driven firmly down the ground and the bowler stops it
short of length outside off, punched down to long off
towards the stumps now and Rahane goes back to whip it to deep square leg
accurate delivery on the stumps, he defends off the back foot
on length on leg stump, tucked away to deep square leg for one
full on middle and leg, tucked away behind square on leg
fullish on the off stump, pushed down back to the bowler
angled in towards middle and leg, steered to midwicket for one
fullish on off, driven to cover and the ball deflects off him to mid-off for one
back of length outside off, punched to cover
almost gets him! Sharp seam movement from just outside off, Rahane left a gap between bat and pad and the ball sneaked in after keeping a bit low also
fuller this time around off, pushed down to mid-on
in the block hole on off, blocked back to the bowler
angled in from back of length towards leg, tucked to square leg for one
doesn't bounce as much as Rahane goes back to cut and the ball goes under the bat
leans forward this time to push the ball on off
flatter on the off stump, he defends it back
fuller delivery on off stump, pushed to cover
full on off, turned away with the wrists to midwicket
full delivery on off and it's defended on the off side
that's gone high, he hasn't timed it well and goes just over extra cover luckily for Vijay. There was width on off and he drove inside out uppishly and the ball just cleared the fielder in the circle
Rahane shows how it's done, takes a step down and drives that in the air over mid-off for a confident four
towards middle stump and he steers to fine leg for one
goes back and defends the length ball to point
length delivery outside off and it's pushed down to mid-off
length ball on the pads, helped to square leg for one
outside the off stump, pushed down to long-off for one
presses forward and blocks the ball
leans into the ball that's on the pads and helps it to short fine leg
uses his wrists this time to turn the ball from middle and leg a bit wide of short fine leg
some room outside off and he guides it towards point for one
on the pads and it's flicked to square leg
length delivery on off, turned between midwicket and mid-on for one
punches the full delivery back to the bowler who gets a hand to it
back of length outside off and it's pushed back to the bowler
shortish on the pads, tucked to deep midwicket for one
full on off, driven down gently to mid-on just past the bowler
short ball coming in, he pivots on the back foot and pulls it nicely to the midwicket boundary for a four
pitches it fuller and it's steered to leg again, for one
flicks it nicely against the turn past midwicket for one
flighted on middle stump, turned to midwicket and Rahane goes back as Raza pounces on the ball
room outside off now and he cuts it to deep point for one
too short outside off, cut off the back foot to off again for one
short on off and turning away, Vijay pulls it off the back foot to long-on for two
flatter outside off, cuts off the back foot to deep cover
room outside off, he cuts off the back foot and comes back just in time for the second run
fuller outside off, pushed to point with the turn
on middle stump now, tucked against the turn with soft hands to the midwicket region to come back for two
goes back in the crease and slaps the ball against the turn to long-ong
length ball just outside off, he leans forward and blocks
more towards middle and leg, helped off the back foot behind square on leg
flighted outside off, pushed into the covers
too short outside off, Vijay cuts easily to deep cover
way too short outside off and Rahane reaches his fifty by whacking that to the midwicket boundary off the back foot
presses forward and helps the ball to point
drives the ball with the turn from outside off to sweeper cover
outside off and turning away and it's cut to deep point for one
full on the stumps and it's driven straight to cover
googly turns in from just outside off, Vijay doesn't pick it and defends off the back foot
full on the stumps again, driven down to long on for one
cuts the ball off the back foot past point and it's in the gap to let them come back for two
what a shot! Rahane reaches out and smacks that through the covers for a cracking four
back of length outside off and it's helped to point for one
beaten outside off as Vijay pokes outside off and misses that one
length ball on the leg stump, helped to midwicket
chipped in the air with a flick towards midwicket and it falls well short
nearly in the block hole and it's flicked to deep backward square leg for two
flight and drift for the full ball to leg stump, he blocks it back
full on leg stump, flicked to deep midwicket for one
googly comes in from well outside off, Rahane cuts off the back foot to deep extra cover
fullish outside off and it's pushed past cover point for one
full on the off stump, pushed down to long on for one
full on the pads, flicked to midwicket off the front foot
room outside off now, Rahane cuts it late to third man for one
some movement away from the batsman as he looked to run it down to third man
back of length on middle stump, tucked off the back foot to deep square leg

that's the first breakthrough, Rahane edged one to cover! Incoming delivery towards the stumps and Rahane closed the face of the bat early, the ball ballooned off the edge to cover for an easy peasy catch
flighted outside off, driven with the turn to long off for one
takes a step down and drives the ball to long off for one
touch back of length on off stump, defends on the leg side
full on middle stump now, driven down to long on this time
comes down the track and drives the ball to long off again
leans into it and helps the ball bit wide of point for one
loud appeal for lbw as Vijay is hit in front of leg while trying to flick that to leg, umpire says not out as it was going down leg
flicked nicely to deep midwicket this time for one
pushes the fullish delivery from outside off wide of mid-off for one
back of length on off now, Vijay defends the ball to point
full on the pads and it's flicked to deep midwicket for his maiden ODI fifty
short of length and Vijay can't clear point, he's annoyed with himself
comes down the track and flicks the ball against the turn just wide of midwicket and far from mid-on for a four
on length on middle and off, he leans forward and blocks
googly turning in from outside off, he chops it wide of point for one
pushes the ball from off to cover for one, and an overthrow at bowler's end gives them another
shorter on the stumps, he goes back and pulls it to deep midwicket for one
flighted on the off stump, driven down to long off for one
angled into the pads, it's flicked to the square leg boundary for one
short of length outside off, he helps it towards point for one
back of length around off, he defends it back
angled into the batsman now, worked past midwicket for one
what a shot! Straight bat offered for the length delivery on off, stood tall and lofted it straight down the ground for a handsome six over long off
steers the ball from outside off to point
gives him the charge and slogs by taking it on the full to the midwicket boundary for four
full on off, punched down to mid-off
back of length outside off and it's chopped to point
on middle and leg and he defends it back to the bowler
back of length on the leg stump and it's steered to deep square leg for one
high and handsome, six more! He didn't have to move much as the ball was pitched up and he drove it straight down to the sight screen
loud appeal as Rayudu is trapped in front and on the back foot as he looked to tuck the ball to leg, the ball angled in but the umpire says no. Very lucky that it wasn't given out, looked out to me
well outside off now, runs it down to third man for one
angled in towards leg, steered to backward square leg for one
back of length outside off, chops it with an inside edge back to the bowler
drives it uppishly and late from outside off, behind square for two
angled in and steered to backward square leg for one
short of length, Vijay swivels on the back foot and pulls to deep square leg
accurate length delivery on the middle stump, blocked back
on off stump, no room again and he defends it back
makes room, Victori chases by pitching it towards the pads and he can't put it away, get a leg bye towards point
back of length on the pads, steers it to square leg for one
full outside off, Rayudu drives nicely and cover dives to get a hand to it but can't stop it
drives firmly and gets an inside edge onto his back pad
comes down and pushes the ball just wide of cover for a quick single

nearly dropped near the boundary, but taken! Vijay lofted the ball very high as it came in, he didn't swing the bat all the way and Waller came under it early, got into position and caught it only after the ball popped out of his hands once.Vijay is very disappointed with himself
right on the off stump and he blocks it back
low full toss on middle and leg, helped down to long on for one

loud appeal for caught behind on his first ball, umpire says no! Everyone around the batsman went up once the ball went behind as Tiwary leaned forward to defend, the ball sneaked through bat and pad and the sound was probably of bat hitting pad
back of length outside off, pushed to cover
outside off now and he runs it down to third man for one
length ball outside off and it's pushed off the front foot into the covers
tries to cut the ball off the back foot outside off, but it goes under the bat to the keeper
back of length and cutting in from outside off, he guides it to third man
full on off, driven down to mid-off and that's drinks
fullish on off stump, presses forward and drives to long-on
pulls his length back a touch, close to off stump. Tiwary is half-forward to block into the covers
full, angling a fair way down the leg side. Tiwary shuffles across too far, can't connect with the flick
back of a length close to off stump. Stands tall and plays with soft hands to drop it a short way into the off side and picks up a quick single
slower ball on off stump, presses forward and pushes down the ground, to the right of mid-off
another slower ball, outside off. Tiwary shuffles down the pitch, doesn't get close to the pitch of the ball, is forced to defend back to the bowler
full and wide and that's a super shot from Tiwary, gets a big stride forward and extends his arms through a drive, lifts it high over mid-off and it soars all the way
back of a length on off stump, lets it come on and pushes it gently to the left of short cover

full outside off and Vitori drops a simple catch at long-on, another let-off for Rayudu. Slogs across the line and hits it to the right of long-on. Didn't have to cover too much ground, and got both hands to it on the dive, but couldn't grab on
fullish on off stump, driven down to long-off
full on off stump, comes forward and whips it down to long-on
on the pads, tucked away towards backward square leg
shortish and slow on middle and leg, Rayudu p;lays a controlled pull towards deep midwicket
sees him shaping to sweep and shortens his length, ends up turning it down the leg side
length ball on leg stump, comes forward and nurdles it around to short fine leg
length ball, goes with the angle towards middle stump, tucked away to deep backward square leg
shortish, angling down leg, goes on the back foot to work it to deep backward square leg
looks to sweep, ball doesn't turn, and he ends up inside-edging onto his pad and the ball rolls away towards cover
full on middle and leg, clipped to short midwicket
full on middle stump, comes forward and pushes it down the ground towards long-on
back of a length outside off, goes back to cut, not enough width, and he chops it down to backward point
full on off stump, whipped to short midwicket, where Chigumbura dives to his left to stop it
full on middle and leg, makes a bit of room and drives inside-out to the right of a diving short extra cover fielder
length ball on off stump, stretches out and whips it into the gap to the left of deep midwicket
charges down and smacks the ball down to long on for one
leans forward and defends the ball to midwicket
goes back in the crease to defend in front of the stumps and gets an edge to cover
goes back again, this time the ball is on leg and he helps it with the turn for one
takes a step down to push the ball to long off for one
length ball on the pads, steered to short fine leg
angles it in on full length and it's flicked towards midwicket for one
full on leg, driven down to long on for one
slower offcutter coming in, he waits and defends it back
angles it in again, slightly overpitched and it's flicked to deep midwicket
goes back for the short ball well outside off and pulls it to deep midwicket
slower ball just outside leg, pushed down to long on for one
flattish on middle stump, he comes down and drives to long off for one
charges down and hammers that just over Rayudu's head to long off
slow and on length on leg, swept with the turn to fine leg
full on off, pushed back to the bowler
on length outside off, driven to sweeper cover off the front foot
tries to go for a six on the leg side and he's taken! He came down, heaved the length delivery from leg stump but Waller took a comfortable catch at deep midwicket, a few yards inside the boundary
full on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket for one
back of length and angled in, worked away to the leg side for one
Tiwary goes as well, straightforward catch to short fine leg! Tiwary shuffled towards off with a step down and flicked the ball late on leg, but straight to Vitori
this one's on leg and he steers it to deep backward square leg in the gap for two
loud appeal for lbw as this one nips in sharply from outside off, Binny looked to defend and the ball deflected off the pad to third man. Height might have been a factor, and it's given as runs
angling in and he flicks that in the air, just over midwicket for one
touch short of length outside off, nudges it off the back foot to point
tucks the length delivery on the stumps to deep square leg
just outside off, he reverse-sweeps and it goes fine on the off side for four even though two fielders chase and slide
comes down and gets a thick edge towards point for one
errs down the leg side for a wide
turning towards leg again, he goes back and swats it well wide of deep square leg for four more!
leans forward and blocks the ball to cover this time
shuffles to off and pushes the ball between cover and cover point for one
offcutter coming in from short of length, Uthappa helps it to third man for one
slower short ball on leg as he came down the track, Binny can only help it towards backward square leg
just outside off, not much room and he defends towards point for one
full and slightly wide, driven nicely to sweeper cover for one
slow offcutter coming in from short of length, tucked towards point for a quick single
slightly wide and he mistimes while looking to drill it down the ground
width again, well outside off and it's slammed with a drive to sweeper cover
comes down to drive the low full toss to cover for one
shuffles across a bit to tuck the back of length ball to midwicket for one
full and wide well outside off, called a wide too

what a yorker, the crowd erupts, Madziva is running around! Uthappa looked to play it off the front foot as the ball came in sharply and knocked the off stump over. Sent it for a walk actually. Umpires check for a no ball and it's fine
the ball is angled in and he flicks it with the wrists to deep midwicket for one
pretty wide outside of, he guides the ball to third man and they want a second. A very wide and inaccurate throw gives them two eventually
big swing for the widish ball outside off, he misses it completely
back of the hand slower ball on short of length outside off, pulled to deep midwicket for one
pretty wide, Binny sees room and opens up his arms drive that through the covers before a fielder cuts it in
takes the pace off again for this one outside off, he guides it gently towards short third man for one
in the block hole on off, helped towards point for one
full toss on the pads, worked with soft hands towards midwicket so that they can come back for the second
full toss just outside off now, driven to sweeper cover for one
full and wide, looking for the yorker, Binny drives it uppishly and late, to send it flying over point for four
on the pads and it's tucked to short fine leg for one
big drive from Jadhav this time, full again with room and Jadhav swung his arms to send that along the ground through the covers for four
tries to swat the short of length ball to leg and manages a thin edge towards short fine leg for one
that's a wide down the leg side and swings a bit just before reaching the keeper who can't stop it with his right hand after moving to his left, it bounces just before him and goes for four
guides the ball to third man from outside off and a direct hit from there breaks the middle stump, the batsman was well inside
nearly in the block hole on off, driven late to deep point for one
full again on off, punched down to long-on for one
full toss, Binny smashes it down the ground but doesn't get enough and Raza takes an impressive catch at long on while diving forward
full on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket and they settle for one
low full toss outside off, he finds point but they sneak in a single

Madziva has his third wicket, top edge from Jadhav after he came to the off side for a wild slog, and the ball went high just behind the stumps on the off side. Enough time for the keeper to come under it
he heaves the fullish delivery, thick leading edge flies away towards sweeper cover for one
full delivery well outside off, Axar drives to cover and makes it just in time at the bowler's end. Wasn't a direct hit either
full delivery is lofted down the ground and it reaches the fielder after a bounce
number four for Madziva as another one holes out! He took the pace off the ball and pitched it on length, Axar heaved, sent it very high and Raza took another easy catch
swinging in towards middle, driven to long on and they come back for the second
straight delivery is pushed down to mid-on
nice shape this time outside the off stump, left alone easily
touch wider outside off, he touched it late to third man for one
swings it in nicely from back of length outside off, Chibhabha shoulders arms
into the batsman this time, tucked towards midwicket for one
shapes it away this time from length to the keeper, he lets it go
swings the short ball away from the batsman who cuts it to point
on length this time and swinging away again, Chamu lets it go
keeps low outside the off stump as Chamu goes back to defend the outswinger, but it beats him
back of length and much closer to off, turned to midwicket
misses again as the ball shapes away nicely from outside off, he cuts and doesn't connect
back of length outside off, punched to cover
right on the off stump, the batsman blocks it back
solid defence for the slightly short of length delivery on the off stump
pretty full now outside off, he looks to play and then lets it go
right on target on the off stump again, defends it to cover
on length and outside off, not much swing and it's left alone
good bounce to end the over as the straight delivery outside off is left again. Maiden over
tries to hammer that ball into the covers but doesn't middle it
short of length and Chamu gets on top of that to punch that past backward point for a cracking four
another one with room, even shorter, and it's cut squarer now for four more
on the leg side now - angled in towards the stumps, not much change in the length and Chamu works it away with great timing to the midwicket boundary
the fours make Dhawal bowl a wide on the off side with some outswing
lesser room, short of length outside off, punched to cover
steers the ball late from outside off to third man for one
outside off, not much room and he helps it to point
towards the off stump and he works it to the leg side by shuffling across, and even comes back for the second
this time it's four, great timing and work off the back foot! It wasn't too much to the leg side, was around off actually, and he covered the stumps to tuck it to the midwicket boundary for four
short of length well outside off, cuts it late to third man for one
still wide outside off, good bounce and he lets it go
comes towards the off stump to probably negate the swing and pushes it to mid on for one
gone, Vusimuzi hands it straight to the fielder! It was pitched up, he drove on the up off the front foot and gave a straightforward catch to point
back of length and coming in, tucked towards backward square leg for one
touch short of length outside off pushed to cover point
back of length outside off, defends it back to the bowler
fuller outside off, he watches it go to the keeper
fullish on the off side, pushed towards mid-off for a quick single
back of length outside off, pushed back down to mid-off
nice shape, moving away from the batsman after pitching a bit too wide outside off, the batsman moves forward and leaves
much shorter with good bounce outside off, he guides it to point
bouncer from Bhuvi towards middle and leg and Chamu ducks under it

falls short! Short ball outside off, he cut it straight to backward point and the fielder there took his eyes off the ball as the ball bounced in front of him, letting the ball hit him near the foot and deflecting to point
lets the last ball go to the keeper
width on offer and Mount Masakadza crucnhes that square of the wicket off the back foot, past point for four
on the stumps this time, Hamilton defends it back just in time
pretty tight just outside off, he covers the stumps and defends it down
angled into the batsman, worked to the midwicket region for one as the fielder from the deep comes in
short of length outside the off stump, pushed to cover off the back foot
coming in towards the off stump, he offers a straight-bat defence to that
back of length with good bounce outside off, defends it to point this time
fuller delivery outside off, pushed down towards mid-on
nice swing and bounce! Hamilton came down on the off side and offered his bat on the off side, the ball nipped away just a bit to beat him
not this time, gets the edge and he's caught behind! Lovely seam position of the ball, facing the slip, shapes away from the batsman as he opens the face of the bat for a single catch to the keeper
shapes it away nicely again, the batsman almost poked his bat again and withdraw at the last moment
offcutter coming in from just outside off, pushed down to mid-on this time
goes on the back foot and defends that after covering his off stump
angled towards the leg stump, worked to square leg off the back foot
slower offcutter coming in towards off, he defends it back
length delivery on the off stump and he defends carefully again
slow and short of length well outside off, he waits and then cuts to third man for two
pitched up outside off with some outswing, he drives that on the up and in the air, right in between cover point and point for four
nice shape from a touch short of length, he nearly his withdrew his bat as the ball shaped away and get a thick edge to third man for one
angling in this time towards the hips, gets a leg bye towards square leg
slow and pretty wide, it's pitched up too and Elton creams that through the covers off the front foot with a beautiful cover drive
good shape away from the batsman, he defends away from the body at the last moment

stunning catch from Jinxy cat! Elton stayed back for the short of length ball as it shaped away, poked and get a thick edge towards second slip actually and Jinxy leapt like a cat to his right to grab that with both hands. Umpires checking for no ball, and if the catch is clean. Not a no ball, and the umpires checking if the ball touched the ground when Rahane landed after his inter-galatic leap. The ball was mainly in his right hand when the elbows hit the ground and looks like some fingers were under the ball. Elton has to go back
sharp turn towards the batsman from outside off, he goes back and helps it behind square on leg
length delivery outside off, pushed into the covers
flighted and full on off, pushed back to the bowler
thick edge all along the ground as he leans forward to play it with the spin to point
much straighter on off stump, he presses forward and blocks
drives away from the body as the ball is pitched outside off and finds one
fullish and swinging in, clipped to midwicket
back of length and well outside off, he cuts it late to third man for one
much straighter outside off, he lets it go
shaping away with room well outside off, he drives it away from the body and gets an inside edge to fine leg boundary for four
back of length and closer to off and he defends off the back foot
fuller on middle, clipped to deep midwicket for one
turning in towards the batsman, helps it to deep midwicket for one

dropped after a mix up! Sean lofted that after coming down the track, went over the covers. Rahane called for it running backward, Tiwary ran in, even got his hands to it but nearly collided with the captain
leans frward a bit and pushes the ball into the covers
stays back and steers the ball to sweeper cover for one
turns it in towards off, Chamu goes back and cuts to deep point for one
stays in the crease and defends the length ball in front of the stumps
on length and outside off, he lets it go
slightly closer to the off stump, he defends it back
looks to whips the short of length ball to leg off the back foot, but ends up defending it back
much straighter outside off, leaves it alone
pitched up slightly and it's driven nicely to deep cover for one
pretty accurate on the off stump, he defends it down the ground
turning in sharply, Chamu helps it to square leg for one
comes down to take it on the full and drives to cover

nicely bowled outside the off stump, nice flight as Sean leaned forward towards the ball and missed
leans into it again and pushes to cover this time
slightly full outside off, he drives it straight to cover again and that's drinks
keeps low outside the off stump after pitching on length, the batsman drives and misses
punches it to cover off the back foot

short, wide and shaping away, he cuts it fiercely to point, he gets a hand to it and they come back by the time third man throws it. Oh, he's thrown it very wide and it goes for overthrows too

drives that past cover for two

oh looks like he's run out with a direct hit! Sikandar went deep in the crease to turn the ball to midwicket and said no only after taking a couple of steps. Chamu had come way out of the crease by now, nearly haflway down, and his dive also could not save him because of Rahane's direct hit. Jinxy the cat
works the ball to leg off the back foot
goes back and cuts the ball to point

he's edged, he's dropped, no he's taken in fact, umpire says no but he walks! Sikandar cut off the back foot as the ball came in, got an edge and the ball lobbed off the keeper's pads square of the wicket and Robbie dived to his right to catch that. Umpire didn't move but Sikandar walked back

that's it, taken at mid-off, and India finish it off. It was pitched up slightly, Donald chipped it down in the air and Axar had to dive forward to get his hands under it. Good catch seals the series win
